Performed an in-depth exploratory analysis on 1,556 daily Bitcoin price records using Python, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn, and Plotly. Identified key trends, volatility patterns, and time-based price movements.
  Discovered that Bitcoin's highest price growth occurred in Q4 2017, with an average daily price change of 1.61% and significant volatility, with daily swings reaching ¬±547.71. 
  Used log scaling for better early-stage trend visualization and candlestick charts for OHLC price comparison. 
  Delivered data-driven insights for financial decision-making.

